{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we address the problems of over-smoothing in GNNs, which is a major barrier to increasing the number of model layers.",
    "The DenseGNN overcomes this problem by fusing the DCN design, enabling the construction of very deep networks while avoiding performance degradation.",
    "The DenseGNN has achieved success in the fields of materials science, molecular, and chemistry, demonstrating its advantages in handling complex many-body interactions and improving training efficiency.",
    "Despite the outstanding performance of DenseGNN on benchmark datasets in multiple domains, we recognize that there are still some potential problems and challenges that need to be addressed in future research.",
    "First, the deep network structure of DenseGNN may face higher computational complexity when dealing with large-scale graph data."
  ]
}